Analyze model coverage as well as code coverage for Software-in-the-Loop (SIL) and 
Processor-in-the-Loop (PIL) generated code, if applicable. 
To use Simulink Coverage in lieu of third-party 
code coverage tools to analyze SIL/PIL code coverage, the 
Code Generation option 'Third-party tool' must be set to 'None'.
Automatically save coverage data results to file.
Directory in which coverage output files will be saved.
Name of file to which coverage data results will automatically be saved.
Enable the collection of model coverage data for this model during simulation.
Model path of the subsystem for which the software gathers and reports coverage data.
Name of workspace variable to which the software saves the results of the last coverage run.
cvdata objects containing additional model coverage data to include in the model coverage report.
Order-independent characters which specify enabled coverage metrics and options.
Full path of the filter file that specifies model objects to exclude from model coverage collection during simulation. Only files that have the valid .cvf filter file format can be used.
Display options for the resulting model coverage report.
Append numerals to the workspace variable names for each\nnew result so that earlier results are not overwritten.
Create an HTML report containing the coverage data at the end of simulation.
Provide coverage data for every block in the model that collects coverage,\nignoring the value of the Simulink block reduction parameter.
Accumulate model coverage results from successive simulations. Set this and CovSaveCumulativeToWorkspaceVar to 'on' to collect model coverage results for multiple simulations in one cvdata object.
Accumulate and save the results of successive simulations in the workspace variable specified by CovCumulativeVarName.
Save the results of the last coverage run in the workspace variable specified by CovSaveName.
Name of workspace variable to which the software saves the results of successive simulation runs.
Display the coverage results from successive simulations in the report. If set to 'off', the software displays the coverage results for the last simulation in the report.
When the simulation is paused, update the model coverage report with coverage results up to the current pause or stop time.

Enable the collection of model coverage data for referenced models during simulation when set to 'on' or 'all'. If set to 'filtered', coverage data is collected for all referenced models except those specified by the parameter CovModelRefExcluded. If set to 'off', coverage data is not collected for referenced models.
Comma-separated list of referenced models for which coverage is disabled.
Enable coverage for any external MATLAB functions called by MATLAB\nfunctions for code generation in your model. The functions can be\ndefined in a MATLAB Function block or in a Stateflow chart.
Enable coverage for C/C++ S-Function blocks in your model.
Absolute tolerance value for relational boundary coverage of floating point inputs.
Relative tolerance value for relational boundary coverage of floating point inputs.
Restrict coverage recording to a specified time interval.
Start time of coverage recording interval.
Stop time of coverage recording interval.
Enable coverage for objective and constraint blocks used by Simulink Design Verifier.
